The paper discusses a method for semi-supervised learning on small labeled datasets using a master-teacher-student model framework. This involves iterative model evolution and confident sample discovery. The paper uses image datasets such as CIFAR-10, which suggests that it may belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. However, the method is also applicable to other types of datasets, which could place it in the machine learning (cs.LG) or artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the use of natural language processing (NLP) datasets, which could place it in the computational linguistics (cs.CL) sub-category. Finally, the paper uses neural networks, which suggests that it may also belong to the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
